## ChkTeX configuration for CTU thesis
## Suppresses false-positive warnings specific to this project.
##
## Note: LaTeX Workshop invokes chktex with -wall, which re-enables every
## warning.  The suppressions below therefore also appear as -nN flags in
## .vscode/settings.json under latex-workshop.linting.chktex.exec.args.
## This file is used when running chktex directly from the command line.

Silent {
    1   ## Command terminated with space
        ## False positives: \tikzexternalize, \phantomsection, \acro*
        ## macros, and \let chains at end of line.
    13  ## Intersentence spacing (`\@`) should perhaps be used
        ## Modern typography/style preference only; this project intentionally
        ## does not enforce explicit sentence-spacing control after abbreviations.
    8   ## Wrong dash length
        ## Czech typography: -- (n-dash) is correct for separating items
        ## and list entries; chktex incorrectly expects --- (em-dash).
    9   ## Bracket mismatch
        ## False positives inside acro package macros:
        ## \acroifanyT{foreign,extra}{(} and {)}.
    21  ## This command might not be intended
        ## \let\Author\@author, \let\Title\@title, \let\Course\@course
        ## are intentional macro aliases defined after \author/\title/\course.
    24  ## Delete space to maintain correct pagereferences
        ## \label appears on its own line after \printbibliography,
        ## \input, and \listoffigures -- this is intentional and correct.
    25  ## You might wish to put this between a pair of `{}`
        ## False positive for \begin{equation}\label{...}.
    31  ## This text may be ignored
        ## False positive on grouped TikZ wrappers ending with `}}`.
    36  ## Put a space after/in front of parenthesis
        ## False positives in enumitem options and Czech list syntax.
    46  ## Use \( ... \) instead of $ ... $
        ## Style preference only; project keeps `$...$` in inline math.
}
